\drawChessboard{rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1}
\end{document}
```

Note that this code is just an example, and you may need to modify it to suit your specific needs. Also, keep in mind that drawing chessboards and pieces in LaTeX can be quite slow and resource-intensive, especially for large boards or complex positions.

